<h1>Wontons and Veggies in Curry Broth</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>8 ounces mushrooms, sliced</li>
<li>1 tablespoon red curry paste</li>
<li>1 14-ounce can coconut milk</li>
<li>2 cups chicken broth</li>
<li>1 tablespoon soy sauce</li>
<li>1 tablespoon fish sauce</li>
<li>1 24-ounce bag frozen mini wontons, potstickers, or dumplings (about 60 mini, or 20 regular size)</li>
<li>3 ounces spinach, chopped</li>
<li>1 tablespoon rice wine vinegar</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li>Warm a large pot or saucepan over medium-high heat.</li>
<li>Add mushrooms and saut√© until golden and tender, 4 to 5 minutes, until liquid evaporates.</li>
<li>Stir in curry paste and cook 30 seconds until fragrant.</li>
<li>Add coconut milk, broth, soy sauce, and fish sauce. Bring to a simmer.</li>
<li>Drop in frozen wontons, bring to a simmer, and simmer for 5 minutes.</li>
<li>Stir in spinach and rice wine vinegar.</li>
<li>Taste and adjust with more soy sauce or vinegar as needed.</li>
<li>Ladle into bowls and top with chili crisp if desired.</li>
</ol>
